RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 80000. (UP TO $13,920 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SYSTEMIC CHANGE rounded most of the first turn in the two path then moved to the three path, tracked the pace on the outside, made a bid under urging leaving the backstretch, vied in the three path around the far turn, took the lead into upper stretch, dueled outside of the runner-up to the wire and narrowly prevailed. KAON lost his footing slightly at the start but broke with the field, brushed with a rival into the first turn, dropped from the four path to the two path around that bend, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked under threat while two path to the inside on the far turn, lost the advantage to the winner into upper stretch, fought gamely inside of that foe to the wire and just missed while well clear for the place. CORTON CHARLEMAGNE was hustled from the gate, dropped back while crowded and taken up against the rail early on the first turn, saved ground through that bend, was coaxed along towards the front, chased while moving from the rail to the four path around the final turn, chased the leading duo into upper stretch and weakened while clear for the show. ALTERNATE REALITY was taken in hand while in tight against the rail early, moved out into the first turn, went two to three wide around that bend, was urged along on the backstretch, went three then four wide on the far turn, moved out some in upper stretch, drifted in around the sixteenth-pole and failed to threaten. CHESS SPECTACULAR bumped with a rival at the start, brushed with another foe into the first turn, dropped from the five path to the three path early on that bend, fell back awkwardly while disliking the kickback when the pacesetter crossed in front later on that bend then moved to the four path, was coaxed down the backstretch, traveled around the far turn in the two path and came up empty. RAPPER ZAPPER bumped with an opponent at the start, dropped in entering the first turn, went three to four wide around most of that bend then moved to the two path, was coaxed at the rear, saved ground on the far turn and showed little.

ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight early,2-3p1st,urged,3-4w2nd turn,drift in1/16,no threat

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CENTRAL PRIDE was bumped at the start, went to the front, set the pace under pressure to his outside, vied in the two path while asked on the turn, shook clear in upper stretch, responded well under a right-handed crop into the final furlong and drew off under a strong hand-ride. EIGHT AND SAND bumped with a rival at the start, pressed the pace on the outside then in the three path around the turn, lost touch with the winner under a drive in upper stretch and proved no match while able to hold the place. I CAN SEE THAT bumped twice with a rival after the start then dropped back, went around the turn in the three path and just missed the place while clear for the show. QUACKENBUSH was hustled from the start then urged along on the outside, went around the turn in the two path and came up empty. RHUM PRESSURE was reluctant to load, bumped with a foe at the start then was hustled, pressed then chased the pace on the outside, dropped back in the four path around the turn, spun five wide into the stretch and tired. FORWARD CAST broke in and bumped with a foe, came out and bumped twice with another opponent shortly thereafter, dropped well behind the rest of the field, saved ground around the turn, angled out in upper stretch, dropped in late and was no factor. THIRTY OYSTERS was urged along off the pace, saved ground on the turn and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD BANKER dropped from the four path to the two path early on the first turn then moved to the three path, tracked outside on the backstretch, was roused near the half-mile pole, issued a challenge in the three path around the far turn, gained the lead near the quarter-pole, fought outside of two opponents into the final sixteenth and proved best under good handling. OPTIC WAY prompted the pace in the two path around the first turn, took the lead inside the three-quarter pole, lost the advantage while asked along the rail on the far turn, fought on well to near the sixteenth-pole but was outfinished while just able to get the place. PIT BOSS was restless in the gate, went three wide on the first turn, stalked the pace on the outside, was urged along in the two path while getting a slight advantage on the final turn, lost the lead between foes near the quarter-pole, kept on well to near the sixteenth-pole but was out-kicked then just missed the place but was clear for the show. CARIBBEAN (AUS) dropped back in the two path early on the first turn, moved to the three then four path later on that bend, settled outside down the backstretch, was ridden along while three then two wide on the far turn and failed to rally. CAERUS stumbled at the start and was off slow, saved ground on the first turn, was rated off the pace, dropped back under urging in the two then three path around the final turn and came up empty. THERISASTORMBREWIN went to the front, showed the way on the inside, lost the advantage inside the three-quarter pole, dropped back late on the backstretch and retreated.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAME CINCO pressed the pace between foes, chased two then three wide around the turn, pursued the runner-up under a drive in the stretch, was guided in closer to that foe while gaining late and just got up under strong urging to narrowly prevail. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Tha n Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIMPLY settled off the pace, moved in near the three-quarter pole, was urged along in the two path around the turn, came out while rallying into upper stretch, closed strongly to get a short lead at the eighth-pole, fought with the runner-up while inside that foe in the final furlong and gamely prevailed under strong urging. MASON MANIA settled off the pace, was roused while moving from the two path to the four path around the turn, rallied five wide into the stretch, closed well to make a bid at the eighth-pole, battled outside of the winner in the final furlong and was denied while clear for the place. GOLDEN CODE showed early speed on the inside of a foe, moved out entering the main-track then stalked on the outside, made a bid outside of the leader at the five-eighths, took a short lead near the half-mile pole, vied in the two path around the turn, was headed in the three path into the stretch, battled under a drive into the final furlong and weakened but held for a share of the show. SAFALOW'S MISSION moved out early, raced up close to the pace, made a bid late on the backstretch, was asked in the three path on the turn, spun four wide into the stretch, battled under a drive into the final furlong and tired but also shared the show. SON OF AN EX showed no speed, raced well back in the field, went three then four wide on the turn, came six wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. FOREVER WICKED lacked early speed, went five to six wide around the turn, came seven wide into the stretch and was no factor. DATESFREEDOM settled of the pace, was urged four then five wide around the turn and failed to respond. MAJESTIC TIGER was forwardly placed on the outside, came under urging in the four path around the turn and had nothing left. BOBBY BO angled in while going to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, lost the lead near the half-mile pole, came up empty along the rail on the turn and retreated then was eased but walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER QUALITY went straight to the front, opened up a sizable advantage, went around the turn in the two path, was let out some late on that bend, had the rider remain motionless in the saddle during the stretch drive and won handily. STAR ATTITUDE was urged along off the pace, went three then four wide around the turn and missed the place while clear for the show. MISBEHAVED was off slow and spotted the front several lengths, raced on the outside under urging, moved in leaving the backstretch, went three then two wide around the turn and was no factor. JOHNSELECTRICRIDE was coaxed along off the pace, dropped well behind while inside early on the turn, floated out to the five path late on that bend and faltered. THE COBBLER stumbled badly at the start and unseated the rider.
